  "text": "Prometheus metric naming convention enforcement is implemented across multiple files in the prometheus/prometheus repository. The validation mechanisms include three key aspects:\n\n1. **Metric Name Validation (UTF-8 compliance)**: Implemented in model/textparse/protobufparse.go (line 451) using model.UTF8Validation.IsValidMetricName() and in model/labels/labels_common.go (line 123) for label values that represent metric names.\n\n2. **Label Name Validation**: Enforced across multiple files:\n   - model/labels/labels_common.go (line 127): IsValidLabelName() for label validation\n   - storage/remote/codec.go (line 857): validateLabelsAndMetricName() for remote read operations\n   - config/config.go (line 635): GlobalConfig.Validate() for external labels validation\n   - model/rulefmt/rulefmt.go (line 121): Rule validation for alert and recording rule labels\n   - model/relabel/relabel.go (lines 140, 159, 168): Relabeling config validation\n   - prompb/io/prometheus/client/decoder.go (line 245): Protobuf label decoding validation\n   - promql/engine.go (line 1933): PromQL aggregation label validation\n   - promql/functions.go (line 1990): label_replace() function validation\n\n3. **Help Text Presence and UTF-8 Validation**: Implemented in text parsing:\n   - model/textparse/openmetricsparse.go (line 512): Help text UTF-8 validation\n   - model/textparse/promparse.go (line 353): Help text UTF-8 validation\n   - model/textparse/protobufparse.go (line 454): Help text UTF-8 validation for protobuf format\n\n4. **Unit Suffix Validation**: Implemented in model/textparse/openmetricsparse.go (lines 525-527) where unit suffix must match the metric name with underscore separator pattern.\n\nThe validation is performed using standardized validation schemes from prometheus/common/model (model.UTF8Validation and model.LegacyValidation) and custom validation logic. All metric names, label names, and help text are validated during parsing and registration phases to ensure compliance with Prometheus naming conventions. The label names and values are also validated against UTF-8 encoding standards and format requirements across remote writes, rule files, relabeling configurations, and PromQL operations."
}

